{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow the same cancellation method for online subscriptions and auto-renewals",
        "additional_details": "Phone calls often take in excess of 30 minutes and in some cases are used to exert undue pressure on people to stay. If a company wants to allow simple online sign up then logically it should be a requirement that accounts can then be managed and cancelled online also. Such a law would encourage excellent digital practices. Companies wishing to only allow phone cancellation would only be allowed to offer phone sign up so it would be a clear and consistent user experience.",
        "background": "Many companies still require customers to phone in order to cancel subscriptions and auto renewals despite allowing new customers to sign up online. Please can you make it a legal requirement to allow online cancellation methods such as via online account or email if online sign up available.",
